1. Creat repository on hithub.com
  * click 'new' 
  * choose public/private
  * added Python gitignore
  * MIT licencse
  
2. From terminal (ideally within a 'repositories' directory, enter command:
      $ git clone https://github.com/<girhub user name>/<repo name>.git
    This copies the repo from github.com to my computer.
3. Edited some file, save changes to local computer.
4. Commit those changes to local repository:

      $ git commit -am 'something interesting'
      
5. Now, sync back to girhub:

      $ git push
